Sleight of hand generally refers to the digital dexterity behind magic tricks and illusions.  Sleight of hand can also be used as a general term for magic and card tricks.

Individual sleight of hand techniques can be called "moves", "techniques", or even just "secrets".  Contrary to popular beliefs, though, most tricks work through the use of only a few moves.  

The "magicians code" would naturally state that I'm not at liberty to reveal these moves.  However, if you are interested in magic, I can recomend sources:

-Bobo's Modern Coin Magic - coin sleights

-Royal Road to Card Magic - card sleights

-Born to Perform - card sleights (Royal Road to Card Magic probably has more tricks and techniques, but Royal Road to Card Magic can be a bit dry and boring.  Born to Perform is an excellent DVD and contains just about all of the essential beginner sleights.)

The first to will probably be available for about $10 at your local Borders.  The last one will be about $30, and can be found at www.penguinmagic.com, also a source for all sorts of tricks and books.